    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>8th Apl 64</date>.</p>
            <p>The <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir—</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">About a fortnight<lb/> since I sent to you a portion of<lb/> my
                fathers Biography. Please<lb/> let me know whether you received<lb/> it. I entrusted
                it to my brother-<lb/>in-law, <persName>Mr Abm Joseph</persName>, who<lb/> mailed it
                for me in <placeName>New York</placeName> to<lb/> your address. As I should not<lb/>
                like to lose the M. S.—not having<lb/> a complete copy of it—please inform<lb/> me
                at your earliest convenience<lb/> whether you received it, so that<lb/> I may act
                accordingly.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please inform me at the<lb/> same time what your prayer<lb/> books
                are, the set, in your currency</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p><hi rend="underline">in sheets</hi>, and bound in the ordinary<lb/> binding; also
                what the price of<lb/> ten sets would be both in sheets<lb/> and bound. Please let
                me<lb/> hear soon from you &amp; oblige.</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="Envelope—Recto"/>
            <p>The <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>1275 Walnut Street</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>Pa.</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
